"Rosemary? Yeah, I saw her talking to Mr. Watercress earlier. No idea what about, though—he’s always got something weird going on."

He wipes down the counter, then adds with a smirk, "My aunt—Ms. Greene—calls him ‘a man with too many projects and not enough sense.’"

"But hey," he shrugs, "he’s been around forever, and people seem to listen to him."
